column1: DAVID:  I'm, I'm trying to finish up.  I mean it's --
DAVID: Oh, yeah. I'm trying, trying to get it done. It's, it's raining outside, isn't it?
HENRY: Well, I'm inside of a room. I can't really -- I don't have a window.
DAVID: Well, that's, that's heavy rain.
DAVID: Yeah. Okay, yeah. Let me finish this up, and I'll get right with you. Call me in about another 15 minutes, okay? We should --
HENRY: Okay. You -- and we're still on-line for the rest of the stuff. That is I mean we still have the two women and, and two, and two kids that will --
DAVID: Right. Yeah, they said they'll do  it.
DAVID: Okay. Let me get back on this then.
DAVID: Oh, boy. I feel like I did a boxing  match.
HENRY: Okay. Now try to keep it short  because, you know, the, these people are not going to want to play something that's real long, okay?
DAVID: I mean how long do they want it to be?
HENRY: Well, you know, remember the, the thing that you did for Jim before?
HENRY: About half a page or so. You know, you --
HENRY: You, you don't have to make it that short. But you know --
HENRY: But, but don't make it like a half hour or something like that.
DAVID: Like I said, I have to make it-- at least wanted to make the point, okay?
HENRY:  I'll talk to you later.  Bye.
